Package edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.FinalProject

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddAmmoPowerUp
    This class will be used to generate objects that represent specific powerup in the game that adds a single bullet to the player's Gun.
    Area
    This class represents a space on the map.
    Game
    (@link Game) is the class that contains the entire program, where we combine our work to create our game as intended.
    GUIClass
    This class will represent the GUI window that will appear if the user decides to run the game in GUI mode.
    Gun
    This class will generate a single object per game representing the player's single gun.
    Holocron
    This is the Holocron class.
    InvincibilityPowerUp
    The InvincibilityPowerUp extends Item, so that it can have a location on the map.
    Item
    This is the top class, Item.
    Jedi
    The Jedi object represents the enemy in the game.
    Map
    This class represents the Map in which the player will interact with.
    Person
    (@link Person) is the superclass of (@link Player) and (@link Jedi) that has the field (@link #location).
    Player
    The Player object represents the user who is playing the game.
    RadarPowerUp
    (@link radarPowerUp) class will activate the radar for the user that picks up the power up.
    Save
    This class will hold all of the objects and data that will need to be preserved if the data is saved in a single (serializable) object that can be saved and then read again later with the use of ObjectInputStream/ObjectOutputStream objects.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    GameOverException
    This exception will be called when the game ends by either the player finding the holocron, or by the player losing all his or her lives.
